The Wallet Custody System: Real platforms split infrastructure into a Hot Wallet (connected online with minimal funds to handle instant user withdrawals) and a Cold Wallet (offline, multi-signature storage holding 95%+ of user deposits).The Order Book Engine: A high-speed sorting data structure. Buy orders (bids) are sorted descending by price; sell orders (asks) are sorted ascending. Matches occur when a bid price meets or exceeds an ask price.The Database Ledger: Maintains internal user balances. User-to-user trades must never settle directly on the live Bitcoin blockchain in real time because block confirmation times take roughly 10 minutes and incur high network transaction fees. Trades happen instantly inside your internal database ledger, and on-chain settlements occur only when a user requests a withdrawal.Phase 2: Full Python Trading Platform EngineThis production-ready simulation script sets up a multi-user trading platform. It automatically provisions a Bitcoin wallet address for users, accepts mock deposits, tracks limit orders, and mutates user balances natively upon trade execution.pythonimport sys
